column1: Rule 1: Modifiers containing an amino acid structure with a carboxylic acid group and an aromatic ring
column2: Rule 2: Modifiers with a phenyl group directly attached to a carboxylic acid and an electron-donating group
column3: Rule 3: Modifiers containing a hydroxyl group in conjunction with a carboxylic acid and an additional aromatic ring
column4: Rule 4: Modifiers with a sulfur-containing group and an aromatic ring
column5: Rule 5: Modifiers with multiple ether linkages and no additional functional groups
column6: Rule 6: Modifiers with a high degree of fluorination and no additional coordinating groups
column7: Rule 7: Modifiers with an indole or pyridine ring and an additional coordinating group
column8: Rule 8: Modifiers with formyl groups and no additional stabilizing groups
column9: Rule 9: Modifiers with a simple aliphatic chain and a terminal carboxylic acid
column10: Rule 10: Modifiers with both an amino and a carboxylic acid group but lacking aromatic or heterocyclic structures
column11: Rule 11: Modifiers with a carboxylic acid group and an electron-withdrawing group such as a nitro group
column12: Rule 12: Modifiers with a pyridine ring and a carboxylic acid group
column13: Rule 13: Modifiers with a benzofuran structure and a carboxylic acid group
column14: Rule 15: Modifiers with a carboxylic acid group and a methoxy group on an aromatic ring
